# Sentry MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the Sentry MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN - Your Sentry authentication token
#   Generate a token at: https://sentry.io/settings/account/api/auth-tokens/
#   Required scopes: project:read, event:read
#
# SENTRY_ORGANIZATION - Your Sentry organization slug
#   This is the organization name as it appears in your Sentry URLs
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/sentry:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
# SENTRY_URL - Sentry instance URL (default: https://sentry.io)
#   For self-hosted Sentry, set this to your instance URL
#
# Examples:
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=your_auth_token_here
# SENTRY_ORGANIZATION=your-org-name
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/sentry:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
# SENTRY_URL=https://sentry.example.com
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=
SENTRY_ORGANIZATION=
